# GitHub webhook secret — environment file for the khonliang-bus systemd unit.
#
# Generate the value with one of:
#   python -c 'import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(48))'
#   openssl rand -base64 48
#
# Install path (recommended):
#   /etc/khonliang/webhook-secret.env  owned by khonliang:khonliang  mode 0640
#
# This file is referenced by the EnvironmentFile= directive in
# /etc/systemd/system/khonliang-bus.service.d/webhook-secret.conf
# (see khonliang-bus.service.d/webhook-secret.conf.example in this dir).
#
# DO NOT commit the real value. This template ships in the repo only as
# a shape reference.
#
# The value below is intentionally EMPTY so that installing this template
# unedited fails loudly: the bus webhook receiver returns 503 when no
# secret is configured (and ``github_webhook_allow_unsigned`` is not set),
# preventing a forged-event footgun. An operator who ships a copy of
# this file unedited will see a 503 in their first ping delivery rather
# than silently accepting events HMAC-signed with a repo-visible string.

GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
